title: New York Population by Race, by County, US Census 1870
name: New York Population by Race, by County, US Census 1870
description:
1870 Census Data for the Counties of New York State. For each county, this table includes Total Population, and the number of residents who are White, Black or African American ("Colored"), American Indian, and "Chinese."

CAUTION on the "Indian" and "Chinese" variables: 
1) Only American Indians who did NOT live on reservations were counted. There were many uncounted Iroquois (Mohawk, Seneca, Tuscarora, Onondaga, Oneida, and Cayuga) in New York State who lived on reservations in 1870. 
2) The "Chinese" numbers almost certainly represent drastic undercounts.

1870 was the first year that the Census attempted to count any race or ethnicity beside White and Black ("Colored").
